body:
kubelet needs to edit  `/var/lib/docker/containers/<container-id>/resolv.conf`(https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/kubelet/dockertools/manager.go#L1587). Yet `-v /var/lib/docker/:/var/lib/docker:ro` param for containerized kubelet won't allow this, while `-v /var/lib/docker/:/var/lib/docker:rw` should do.

```
$ log for kubelet
{"log":"I1016 06:53:46.433778    8104 kubelet.go:1969] SyncLoop (ADD, \"api\"): \"busybox2_default\"\n","stream":"stderr","time":"2015-10-16T06:53:46.43437725Z"}
{"log":"I1016 06:53:46.439902    8104 manager.go:1714] Need to restart pod infra container for \"busybox2_default\" because it is not found\n","stream":"stderr","time":"2015-10-16T06:53:46.441016223Z"}
{"log":"E1016 06:54:06.571164    8104 manager.go:1606] resolv.conf could not be updated. err:open /var/lib/docker/containers/b2581450deb17be3f77d6dc3b8059c0f08c65836ead9fc0b7bdb52ee16b3a878/resolv.conf: read-only file system\n","stream":"stderr","time":"2015-10-16T06:54:06.573697416Z"}
{"log":"E1016 06:54:06.571264    8104 manager.go:1868] Failed to create pod infra container: open /var/lib/docker/containers/b2581450deb17be3f77d6dc3b8059c0f08c65836ead9fc0b7bdb52ee16b3a878/resolv.conf: read-only file system; Skipping pod \"busybox2_default\"\n","stream":"stderr","time":"2015-10-16T06:54:06.579055226Z"}
{"log":"E1016 06:54:06.586395    8104 pod_workers.go:113] Error syncing pod a5a65d15-73d2-11e5-a924-000c2994ac1c, skipping: open /var/lib/docker/containers/b2581450deb17be3f77d6dc3b8059c0f08c65836ead9fc0b7bdb52ee16b3a878/resolv.conf: read-only file system\n","stream":"stderr","time":"2015-10-16T06:54:06.591349163Z"}
```

I'll send a pr to fix this later.
